+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013ZZnimfjdYKS4ktAyPYYFs","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have now read every file in the repository. Here is the complete analysis.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Codebase Analysis: SSG Toolkit\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .eslintrc.cjs              # ESLint config\n├── .gitignore                 # ignores node_modules/ and dist/\n├── TASK.md                    # Task description\n├── package.json               # Project manifest\n├── package-lock.json          # Lockfile\n├── tsconfig.json              # TypeScript config\n├── vitest.config.ts           # Vitest config\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── index.ts           # Barrel re-exports\n│   │   ├── types.ts           # All type/interface definitions\n│   │   ├── engine.ts          # BuildEngine class\n│   │   └── templates.ts       # Default + list template factories\n│   └── plugins/\n│       └── .gitkeep           # Empty -- plugins not yet implemented\n└── tests/\n    ├── core.test.ts            # 15 core engine tests\n    └── plugins/\n        ├── markdown-ext.test.ts      # 8 tests\n        ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts    # 8 tests\n        ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts  # 8 tests (one is \"does not modify inline code\")\n        ├── taxonomy.test.ts          # 8 tests\n        ├── rss-feed.test.ts          # 7 tests\n        ├── search-index.test.ts      # 7 tests\n        ├── sitemap.test.ts           # 7 tests\n        └── dev-server.test.ts        # 7 tests\n```\n\nThe `src/plugins/` directory is empty (only a `.gitkeep`). All 8 plugins need to be implemented.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Plugin Interface (`/workspace/src/core/types.ts`) -- Every Field and Method\n\n**`SiteConfig`** -- Site-wide configuration:\n- `title: string` -- site title (e.g., \"Test Site\")\n- `baseUrl: string` -- root URL (e.g., \"https://example.com\")\n- `outputDir: string` -- where built files go (e.g., \"./dist\")\n- `contentDir: string` -- source content directory (e.g., \"./content\")\n- `templateDir: string` -- template directory (e.g., \"./templates\")\n\n**`ContentFile`** -- A single piece of content:\n- `slug: string` -- URL-safe identifier (used as output filename: `{slug}.html`)\n- `title: string` -- display title\n- `content: string` -- raw content (markdown or HTML)\n- `metadata: Record<string, unknown>` -- arbitrary key/value pairs\n- `date?: string` -- optional date string\n- `tags?: string[]` -- optional tag list\n- `template?: string` -- optional template name (defaults to `'default'`)\n\n**`BuildContext`** -- Mutable state passed through the entire build pipeline:\n- `config: SiteConfig` -- the site configuration\n- `files: ContentFile[]` -- array of content files (can be mutated by plugins)\n- `output: Map<string, string>` -- output path -> rendered content (plugins add to this)\n- `assets: Map<string, Buffer>` -- output path -> binary data\n- `data: Map<string, unknown>` -- shared plugin data store (plugins communicate via this)\n\n**`PluginHooks`** -- The three lifecycle hooks a plugin can implement (all optional):\n- `beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void` -- runs before content transforms, in dependency order\n- `transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile` -- called once per file per plugin, returns transformed file\n- `afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void` -- runs after template rendering, in dependency order\n\n**`Plugin`** -- The main plugin interface:\n- `name: string` -- unique plugin identifier\n- `version: string` -- semver version string\n- `dependencies: string[]` -- names of plugins this depends on (used for topological sort)\n- `hooks: PluginHooks` -- the hook implementations\n\n**`Template`** -- A rendering template:\n- `name: string` -- template identifier (matched by `ContentFile.template`)\n- `render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string` -- renders content + data to HTML string\n\n---\n\n### 3. Build Engine (`/workspace/src/core/engine.ts`) -- How Plugins are Loaded and Executed\n\nThe `BuildEngine` class has:\n\n**Private state:**\n- `plugins: Plugin[]` -- registered plugins\n- `templates: Map<string, Template>` -- registered templates\n- `config: SiteConfig` -- passed via constructor\n\n**Registration methods:**\n- `registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin): void` -- pushes a plugin onto the `plugins` array\n- `registerTemplate(template: Template): void` -- sets a template in the templates map keyed by name\n\n**`resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]`** -- Topological sort using DFS:\n1. Creates a `pluginMap` from name -> Plugin.\n2. Uses `visited` (fully processed) and `visiting` (in current DFS path) sets.\n3. For each plugin, recursively visits its dependencies first.\n4. If a plugin is in the `visiting` set during recursion, throws `\"Circular dependency detected: {name}\"`.\n5. If a dependency name is not in `pluginMap`, throws `\"Missing dependency: {name} requires {dep}\"`.\n6. Returns the sorted plugin array (dependencies before dependents).\n\n**`async build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>`** -- The core build pipeline:\n\n1. **Create BuildContext** -- copies the files array, initializes empty `output`, `assets`, and `data` Maps.\n2. **Resolve plugin order** -- calls `resolvePluginOrder()`.\n3. **Phase 1: `beforeBuild` hooks** -- iterates ordered plugins, calls `beforeBuild(ctx)` on each.\n4. **Phase 2: `transformContent` hooks** -- iterates ordered plugins; for each plugin with `transformContent`, iterates all files and replaces `ctx.files` with transformed results.\n5. **Phase 3: Template rendering** -- for each file, looks up template by `file.template` (defaults to `'default'`). If template found, calls `template.render(file.content, {...data})` and stores result at `{slug}.html` in output. The data object passed to render includes: `title`, `slug`, `date`, `tags`, spread `metadata`, `siteTitle`, and `baseUrl`. If no matching template, stores raw `file.content` at `{slug}.html`.\n6. **Phase 4: `afterBuild` hooks** -- iterates ordered plugins, calls `afterBuild(ctx)` on each.\n7. Returns the final `BuildContext`.\n\n**Read-only accessors:**\n- `getPlugins(): Plugin[]` -- returns a shallow copy\n- `getTemplates(): Map<string, Template>` -- returns a shallow copy\n\n---\n\n### 4. Template System (`/workspace/src/core/templates.ts`)\n\nTwo factory functions:\n\n**`createDefaultTemplate(): Template`** -- name: `'default'`\nRenders an HTML document with:\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>{data.title} | {data.siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <article>\n    <h1>{data.title}</h1>\n    {if data.date: <time>{data.date}</time>}\n    <div class=\"content\">{content}</div>\n  </article>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n**`createListTemplate(): Template`** -- name: `'list'`\nRenders an HTML document with:\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>{data.title} | {data.siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>{data.title}</h1>\n  <div class=\"list\">{content}</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\nThe barrel export at `/workspace/src/core/index.ts` re-exports: `BuildEngine`, `createDefaultTemplate`, `createListTemplate`, and all types (`BuildContext`, `ContentFile`, `Plugin`, `PluginHooks`, `SiteConfig`, `Template`).\n\n---\n\n### 5. Core Tests (`/workspace/tests/core.test.ts`) -- All 15 Tests\n\nUses helpers: `makeFile(overrides)` (defaults: slug `'test-post'`, title `'Test Post'`, content `'<p>Hello world</p>'`, metadata `{}`) and `makePlugin(overrides)` (defaults: name `'test-plugin'`, version `'1.0.0'`, dependencies `[]`, hooks `{}`).\n\n| # | Test Name | What It Verifies |\n|---|-----------|-----------------|\n| 1 | `registers plugins` | After `registerPlugin`, `getPlugins()` has length 1 and correct name |\n| 2 | `registers templates` | After `registerTemplate(createDefaultTemplate())`, templates map has `'default'` |\n| 3 | `builds with default template and renders HTML` | Output contains `<!DOCTYPE html>`, title `'My Post'`, content `<p>Content here</p>`, site title `'Test Site'` |\n| 4 | `builds with list template and renders list HTML` | Output contains `<!DOCTYPE html>`, title `'My List'`, `<div class=\"list\">`, and list content |\n| 5 | `outputs raw content when no matching template` | With no template registered, output is raw `<p>Raw content</p>` |\n| 6 | `calls plugin beforeBuild hook` | A `beforeBuild` hook setting `called = true` is invoked |\n| 7 | `calls plugin transformContent hook to transform files` | Hook uppercases content; result is `'HELLO'` |\n| 8 | `calls plugin afterBuild hook` | An `afterBuild` hook setting `called = true` is invoked |\n| 9 | `executes plugins in dependency order` | Plugin `b` depends on `a`; resolved order is `['a', 'b']` |\n| 10 | `throws on circular dependency` | `a -> b -> a` throws `'Circular dependency'` |\n| 11 | `throws on missing dependency` | `a -> missing` throws `'Missing dependency'` |\n| 12 | `applies multiple plugins transformContent in order` | Two plugins append `[first]` and `[second]`; result is `'start [first] [second]'` |\n| 13 | `provides shared data store in build context` | `beforeBuild` sets `ctx.data.set('key', 'value')`; verified after build |\n| 14 | `retains file metadata through build` | File with `metadata: {author:'Alice', category:'tech'}`, `date: '2024-01-01'`, `tags: ['js','node']` is preserved |\n| 15 | `produces empty output for empty file list` | Build with `[]` files yields `output.size === 0` and `files.length === 0` |\n\n---\n\n### 6. All Plugin Test Files -- Complete Details\n\n#### 6A. `markdown-ext.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImport: `createMarkdownExtPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/markdown-ext.js`\n\n| # | Test | Input Content | Expectations |\n|---|------|--------------|-------------|\n| 1 | `converts basic markdown to HTML` | `'# Hello\\n\\nThis is a **bold** paragraph.'` | Contains `<h1>`, contains `'Hello'`, contains `<strong>bold</strong>` |\n| 2 | `handles footnotes with [^1] syntax` | `'Some text[^1] here.\\n\\n[^1]: This is the footnote.'` | Contains `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>` |\n| 3 | `renders footnote section at bottom of content` | `'Text[^1] and more[^2].\\n\\n[^1]: First note.\\n[^2]: Second note.'` | Contains `<section class=\"footnotes\">`, `<li id=\"fn-1\">First note.</li>`, `<li id=\"fn-2\">Second note.</li>` |\n| 4 | `converts :::note container to admonition div` | `':::note\\nThis is a note.\\n:::'` | Contains `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">`, contains `'This is a note.'` |\n| 5 | `converts :::warning container to admonition div` | `':::warning\\nBe careful!\\n:::'` | Contains `<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\">`, contains `'Be careful!'` |\n| 6 | `converts :::tip container to admonition div` | `':::tip\\nHelpful hint.\\n:::'` | Contains `<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">`, contains `'Helpful hint.'` |\n| 7 | `preserves existing HTML in content` | `'<div class=\"custom\">Already HTML</div>'` | Contains `'Already HTML'` |\n| 8 | `handles empty content` | `''` | `result.content` is defined |\n\nKey implementation details: Must use the `marked` library for Markdown-to-HTML. Must pre-process footnotes (`[^N]` -> `<sup><a href=\"#fn-N\">N</a></sup>`, collect definitions, render a `<section class=\"footnotes\"><ol>...</ol></section>` at the end). Must pre-process `:::type ... :::` blocks into `<div class=\"admonition admonition-{type}\">...content...</div>`.\n\n---\n\n#### 6B. `asset-pipeline.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImport: `createAssetPipelinePlugin` from `../../src/plugins/asset-pipeline.js`\n\n| # | Test | Input | Expectations |\n|---|------|-------|-------------|\n| 1 | `rewrites relative image URLs to /assets/ path` | `<img src=\"./image.png\" alt=\"test\">` | Contains `src=\"/assets/image.png\"`, does NOT contain `src=\"./image.png\"` |\n| 2 | `rewrites relative link URLs to /assets/ path` | `<a href=\"./doc.pdf\">Download</a>` | Contains `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`, does NOT contain `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` |\n| 3 | `leaves absolute URLs unchanged` | `<img src=\"https://cdn.example.com/image.png\">` | Contains original absolute URL |\n| 4 | `generates asset manifest in ctx.data` | `<img src=\"./photo.jpg\">` | `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` has `assets` containing `'photo.jpg'` |\n| 5 | `handles files with no asset references` | `<p>No assets here</p>` | Content unchanged: `'<p>No assets here</p>'` |\n| 6 | `handles multiple assets in one file` | `<img src=\"./a.png\"><img src=\"./b.jpg\"><a href=\"./c.pdf\">link</a>` | Manifest assets contains `'a.png'`, `'b.jpg'`, `'c.pdf'` |\n| 7 | `asset manifest includes all discovered assets` | Two files: `<img src=\"./one.png\">`, `<img src=\"./two.png\">` (called sequentially on same ctx) | Manifest has length 2, contains both |\n| 8 | `does not double-process already-rewritten URLs` | `<img src=\"/assets/image.png\">` | Content unchanged `'<img src=\"/assets/image.png\">'`; manifest is undefined or has 0 assets |\n\nKey details: Rewrites `./filename` to `/assets/filename` in both `src` and `href` attributes. Stores `{ assets: string[] }` at key `'asset-manifest'` in `ctx.data`. Must accumulate assets across multiple calls on the same context.\n\n---\n\n#### 6C. `syntax-highlight.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImport: `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/syntax-highlight.js`\n\n| # | Test | Input | Expectations |\n|---|------|-------|-------------|\n| 1 | `adds language class to code blocks` | `<pre><code class=\"language-javascript\">const x = 1;</code></pre>` | Contains `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"` |\n| 2 | `adds data-language attribute to pre tags` | `<pre><code class=\"language-python\">print(\"hi\")</code></pre>` | Contains `data-language=\"python\"` |\n| 3 | `handles multiple code blocks in one file` | Two blocks: `language-js` and `language-py` | Contains `data-language=\"js\"` and `data-language=\"py\"` |\n| 4 | `handles code block with no language specified` | `<pre><code>plain code</code></pre>` | Content unchanged exactly; no `highlighted` class added |\n| 5 | `adds highlighted class to processed blocks` | `<pre><code class=\"language-rust\">fn main() {}</code></pre>` | Contains `'highlighted'` |\n| 6 | `preserves code block content` | `<pre><code class=\"language-ts\">const x: number = 42;</code></pre>` | Contains `'const x: number = 42;'` |\n| 7 | `handles empty code blocks` | `<pre><code class=\"language-js\"></code></pre>` | Contains `data-language=\"js\"` and `'highlighted'` |\n| 8 | `does not modify inline code` | `<p>Use <code>console.log()</code> for debugging.</p>` | Content unchanged exactly; no `highlighted` class |\n\nKey details: Only processes `<pre><code class=\"language-XXX\">` patterns. Adds `highlighted` to the class list and adds `data-language=\"XXX\"` to the `<pre>` tag. Leaves `<code>` without `<pre>` wrapper and `<code>` without `language-` class untouched.\n\n---\n\n#### 6D. `taxonomy.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImport: `createTaxonomyPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/taxonomy.js`\n\n| # | Test | Input | Expectations |\n|---|------|-------|-------------|\n| 1 | `builds tag index from file tags` | 2 files: one with `['javascript','node']`, one with `['javascript']` | `taxonomy-tags` map: `javascript` has 2, `node` has 1 |\n| 2 | `generates tag listing pages in ctx.output` | 1 file tagged `['javascript']` | After `beforeBuild` + `afterBuild`: `output.has('tags/javascript.html')` is true, content contains `'Post 1'` |\n| 3 | `handles files with no tags` | 1 file with no tags | Tag map size is 0 |\n| 4 | `handles files with multiple tags` | 1 file tagged `['js','node','web']` | Tag map size is 3, has all three keys |\n| 5 | `tag pages list all files with that tag` | 2 files both tagged `['tech']` | Tag page `'tags/tech.html'` contains both `'First Post'` and `'Second Post'` |\n| 6 | `stores tag map in ctx.data` | 1 file tagged `['alpha']` | `ctx.data.has('taxonomy-tags')` is true |\n| 7 | `handles empty file list` | Empty array | After both hooks: tag map size is 0 |\n| 8 | `tags are case-normalized to lowercase` | Two files: one tagged `['JavaScript']`, other `['JAVASCRIPT']` | Map has `'javascript'` with length 2; does NOT have `'JavaScript'` or `'JAVASCRIPT'` |\n\nKey details: Uses `beforeBuild` to scan `ctx.files` and build a `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` stored at key `'taxonomy-tags'` in `ctx.data`. Tags are lowercased. Uses `afterBuild` to generate HTML tag pages at `tags/{tag}.html` in `ctx.output`, listing all post titles for that tag.\n\n---\n\n#### 6E. `rss-feed.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImport: `createRssFeedPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/rss-feed.js`\nDependencies: `['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy']`\n\n| # | Test | Input | Expectations |\n|---|------|-------|-------------|\n| 1 | `generates valid RSS 2.0 XML` | 1 file with date | Output `'feed.xml'` contains `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>`, `</rss>` |\n| 2 | `feed items contain HTML content not raw markdown` | File with HTML content `<p>This is <strong>HTML</strong> content</p>` | Feed contains `<![CDATA[<p>This is <strong>HTML</strong> content</p>]]>` |\n| 3 | `feed items include category tags from taxonomy` | File tagged `['javascript']`; `ctx.data` has `'taxonomy-tags'` map | Feed contains `<category>javascript</category>` |\n| 4 | `feed includes channel title from config` | Any file | Feed contains `<title>Test Site</title>` |\n| 5 | `feed items sorted by date newest first` | 3 files: dates `2023-01-01`, `2024-06-15`, `2024-01-01` | In feed XML, `'New Post'` index < `'Mid Post'` index < `'Old Post'` index |\n| 6 | `handles files without dates` | File with no date | Feed contains `'No Date Post'`; does NOT contain `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>` |\n| 7 | `feed link uses baseUrl from config` | 1 file slug `'post-1'` | Feed contains `<link>https://example.com</link>` (channel) and `<link>https://example.com/post-1.html</link>` (item) |\n\n---\n\n#### 6F. `search-index.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImport: `createSearchIndexPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/search-index.js`\nDependencies: `['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight']`\n\n| # | Test | Input | Expectations |\n|---|------|-------|-------------|\n| 1 | `generates search-index.json in ctx.output` | 1 file | `output.has('search-index.json')` is true |\n| 2 | `index entries have title, slug, and plain text content` | File with `<p>Some text here</p>` | Parsed JSON entry: `slug === 'my-post'`, `title === 'My Post'`, `content === 'Some text here'` |\n| 3 | `HTML tags stripped from indexed content` | `<h1>Title</h1><p>This is <strong>bold</strong> text.</p>` | Content has no `<` or `>` chars; contains `'bold'` and `'text'` |\n| 4 | `code blocks included in searchable text` | `<pre><code class=\"language-js\">const x = 1;</code></pre>` | Content contains `'const x = 1;'` |\n| 5 | `handles empty file list` | Empty array | Parsed JSON equals `[]` |\n| 6 | `search index is valid JSON` | 2 files | Parsing does not throw; result is array of length 2 |\n| 7 | `index entries include tags if present` | File with `tags: ['js', 'web']` | Parsed entry `tags` equals `['js', 'web']` |\n\n---\n\n#### 6G. `sitemap.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImport: `createSitemapPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/sitemap.js`\nDependencies: `['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']`\n\n| # | Test | Input | Expectations |\n|---|------|-------|-------------|\n| 1 | `generates sitemap.xml in ctx.output` | Output map with `'post-1.html'` | `output.has('sitemap.xml')` is true |\n| 2 | `includes all content page URLs` | Output map with `'post-1.html'` and `'post-2.html'` | Sitemap contains both full URLs with baseUrl prefix |\n| 3 | `includes taxonomy tag page URLs` | Output has `'tags/javascript.html'`; data has taxonomy-tags map | Sitemap contains `'https://example.com/tags/javascript.html'` |\n| 4 | `includes feed.xml URL` | Output has `'feed.xml'` | Sitemap contains `'https://example.com/feed.xml'` |\n| 5 | `URLs use baseUrl from config` | Output has `'about.html'` | Sitemap contains `'https://example.com/about.html'` |\n| 6 | `sitemap is valid XML structure` | Output has `'post.html'` | Contains `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<urlset`, `</urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>` |\n| 7 | `handles site with no tag pages` | Output has `'post.html'`; no taxonomy data | Contains post URL; does NOT contain `'/tags/'` |\n\n---\n\n#### 6H. `dev-server.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImport: `createDevServerPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/dev-server.js`\nDependencies: `['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']`\n\nLocal interface defined in test:\n```typescript\ninterface DevServerConfig {\n  port: number;\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n  assetPaths: string[];\n  searchIndexPath: string;\n}\n```\n\n| # | Test | Input | Expectations |\n|---|------|-------|-------------|\n| 1 | `stores dev-server-config in ctx.data` | Empty ctx | `ctx.data.has('dev-server-config')` is true |\n| 2 | `config includes port setting` | Empty ctx | `config.port` is defined and `typeof` is `'number'` |\n| 3 | `config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline` | Data has `'asset-manifest': { assets: ['image.png', 'style.css'] }` | `config.assetPaths` contains both; routes filtered by `handler === 'asset'` has length >= 2 |\n| 4 | `config includes search index path` | Output has `'search-index.json'` | `config.searchIndexPath === '/search-index.json'` |\n| 5 | `config includes content routes` | Output has `'post-1.html'` and `'post-2.html'` | Routes filtered by `handler === 'static'` has length 2 |\n| 6 | `default port is 3000` | Empty ctx | `config.port === 3000` |\n| 7 | `handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully` | Empty ctx (no asset-manifest) | `config.assetPaths` equals `[]` |\n\n---\n\n### 7. `package.json` Details\n\n- **Name:** `bench-ssg-toolkit`\n- **Type:** `\"module\"` (ESM)\n- **Main:** `dist/core/index.js`\n- **Scripts:**\n  - `build` -> `tsc`\n  - `lint` -> `eslint src/ tests/`\n  - `test` -> `vitest run`\n- **Dev Dependencies:** `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin ^7.18.0`, `@typescript-eslint/parser ^7.18.0`, `eslint ^8.57.1`, `typescript ^5.9.3`, `vitest ^2.1.9`\n- **Dependencies:** `@types/express ^5.0.6`, `@types/marked ^5.0.2`, `express ^5.2.1`, `marked ^17.0.2`\n\n---\n\n### 8. Configuration Files\n\n**`tsconfig.json`:**\n- `strict: true`\n- `target: \"ES2022\"`, `module: \"Node16\"`, `moduleResolution: \"Node16\"`\n- `outDir: \"./dist\"`, `rootDir: \"./src\"`\n- `declaration: true`, `esModuleInterop: true`, `skipLibCheck: true`\n- Includes `src/**/*`\n\n**`.eslintrc.cjs`:**\n- Parser: `@typescript-eslint/parser`\n- Plugins: `@typescript-eslint`\n- Extends: `eslint:recommended`, `plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended`\n- `ecmaVersion: 2022`, `sourceType: \"module\"`\n- Custom rule: `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars` set to `error` with `argsIgnorePattern: '^_'` and `varsIgnorePattern: '^_'`\n- Env: `node: true`, `es2022: true`\n\n**`vitest.config.ts`:**\n- `globals: true` (no need to import `describe`/`it`/`expect`, though the tests do import them)\n- `testTimeout: 10000` (10 seconds)\n\n---\n\n### Plugin Dependency Graph (from TASK.md)\n\n```\nWave 1 (no dependencies):\n  markdown-ext, asset-pipeline, syntax-highlight, taxonomy\n\nWave 2 (depend on Wave 1):\n  rss-feed       -> [markdown-ext, taxonomy]\n  search-index   -> [markdown-ext, syntax-highlight]\n\nWave 3 (depend on Wave 2):\n  sitemap        -> [taxonomy, rss-feed]\n  dev-server     -> [asset-pipeline, search-index]\n```\n\nEach plugin must export a `createXxxPlugin()` factory function returning a `Plugin` object. The total test count target is 15 existing core tests + 60 new plugin tests = 75 passing tests."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2cb177 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 39152\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 145399</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ff94828-5cc0-4291-8ecd-b4f9ec079100","uuid":"64779af3-a7ad-446e-9ef1-299cff18ef51","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore this SSG toolkit codebase. I need to understand:\n\n1. The complete directory structure\n2. The Plugin interface from src/core/types.ts - every field and method\n3. The build engine in src/core/ - how plugins are loaded and executed\n4. The template system\n5. All existing tests in tests/core.test.ts\n6. ALL plugin test files in tests/plugins/ - read every single one completely\n7. The package.json for dependencies and scripts\n8. tsconfig.json and any lint config\n\nRead every file completely - I need full details of every test expectation.","agentId":"a2cb177","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have now read every file in the repository. Here is the complete analysis.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Codebase Analysis: SSG Toolkit\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .eslintrc.cjs              # ESLint config\n├── .gitignore                 # ignores node_modules/ and dist/\n├── TASK.md                    # Task description\n├── package.json               # Project manifest\n├── package-lock.json          # Lockfile\n├── tsconfig.json              # TypeScript config\n├── vitest.config.ts           # Vitest config\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── index.ts           # Barrel re-exports\n│   │   ├── types.ts           # All type/interface definitions\n│   │   ├── engine.ts          # BuildEngine class\n│   │   └── templates.ts       # Default + list template factories\n│   └── plugins/\n│       └── .gitkeep           # Empty -- plugins not yet implemented\n└── tests/\n    ├── core.test.ts            # 15 core engine tests\n    └── plugins/\n        ├── markdown-ext.test.ts      # 8 tests\n        ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts    # 8 tests\n        ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts  # 8 tests (one is \"does not modify inline code\")\n        ├── taxonomy.test.ts          # 8 tests\n        ├── rss-feed.test.ts          # 7 tests\n        ├── search-index.test.ts      # 7 tests\n        ├── sitemap.test.ts           # 7 tests\n        └── dev-server.test.ts        # 7 tests\n```\n\nThe `src/plugins/` directory is empty (only a `.gitkeep`). All 8 plugins need to be implemented.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Plugin Interface (`/workspace/src/core/types.ts`) -- Every Field and Method\n\n**`SiteConfig`** -- Site-wide configuration:\n- `title: string` -- site title (e.g., \"Test Site\")\n- `baseUrl: string` -- root URL (e.g., \"https://example.com\")\n- `outputDir: string` -- where built files go (e.g., \"./dist\")\n- `contentDir: string` -- source content directory (e.g., \"./content\")\n- `templateDir: string` -- template directory (e.g., \"./templates\")\n\n**`ContentFile`** -- A single piece of content:\n- `slug: string` -- URL-safe identifier (used as output filename: `{slug}.html`)\n- `title: string` -- display title\n- `content: string` -- raw content (markdown or HTML)\n- `metadata: Record<string, unknown>` -- arbitrary key/value pairs\n- `date?: string` -- optional date string\n- `tags?: string[]` -- optional tag list\n- `template?: string` -- optional template name (defaults to `'default'`)\n\n**`BuildContext`** -- Mutable state passed through the entire build pipeline:\n- `config: SiteConfig` -- the site configuration\n- `files: ContentFile[]` -- array of content files (can be mutated by plugins)\n- `output: Map<string, string>` -- output path -> rendered content (plugins add to this)\n- `assets: Map<string, Buffer>` -- output path -> binary data\n- `data: Map<string, unknown>` -- shared plugin data store (plugins communicate via this)\n\n**`PluginHooks`** -- The three lifecycle hooks a plugin can implement (all optional):\n- `beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void` -- runs before content transforms, in dependency order\n- `transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile` -- called once per file per plugin, returns transformed file\n- `afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void` -- runs after template rendering, in dependency order\n\n**`Plugin`** -- The main plugin interface:\n- `name: string` -- unique plugin identifier\n- `version: string` -- semver version string\n- `dependencies: string[]` -- names of plugins this depends on (used for topological sort)\n- `hooks: PluginHooks` -- the hook implementations\n\n**`Template`** -- A rendering template:\n- `name: string` -- template identifier (matched by `ContentFile.template`)\n- `render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string` -- renders content + data to HTML string\n\n---\n\n### 3. Build Engine (`/workspace/src/core/engine.ts`) -- How Plugins are Loaded and Executed\n\nThe `BuildEngine` class has:\n\n**Private state:**\n- `plugins: Plugin[]` -- registered plugins\n- `templates: Map<string, Template>` -- registered templates\n- `config: SiteConfig` -- passed via constructor\n\n**Registration methods:**\n- `registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin): void` -- pushes a plugin onto the `plugins` array\n- `registerTemplate(template: Template): void` -- sets a template in the templates map keyed by name\n\n**`resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]`** -- Topological sort using DFS:\n1. Creates a `pluginMap` from name -> Plugin.\n2. Uses `visited` (fully processed) and `visiting` (in current DFS path) sets.\n3. For each plugin, recursively visits its dependencies first.\n4. If a plugin is in the `visiting` set during recursion, throws `\"Circular dependency detected: {name}\"`.\n5. If a dependency name is not in `pluginMap`, throws `\"Missing dependency: {name} requires {dep}\"`.\n6. Returns the sorted plugin array (dependencies before dependents).\n\n**`async build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>`** -- The core build pipeline:\n\n1. **Create BuildContext** -- copies the files array, initializes empty `output`, `assets`, and `data` Maps.\n2. **Resolve plugin order** -- calls `resolvePluginOrder()`.\n3. **Phase 1: `beforeBuild` hooks** -- iterates ordered plugins, calls `beforeBuild(ctx)` on each.\n4. **Phase 2: `transformContent` hooks** -- iterates ordered plugins; for each plugin with `transformContent`, iterates all files and replaces `ctx.files` with transformed results.\n5. **Phase 3: Template rendering** -- for each file, looks up template by `file.template` (defaults to `'default'`). If template found, calls `template.render(file.content, {...data})` and stores result at `{slug}.html` in output. The data object passed to render includes: `title`, `slug`, `date`, `tags`, spread `metadata`, `siteTitle`, and `baseUrl`. If no matching template, stores raw `file.content` at `{slug}.html`.\n6. **Phase 4: `afterBuild` hooks** -- iterates ordered plugins, calls `afterBuild(ctx)` on each.\n7. Returns the final `BuildContext`.\n\n**Read-only accessors:**\n- `getPlugins(): Plugin[]` -- returns a shallow copy\n- `getTemplates(): Map<string, Template>` -- returns a shallow copy\n\n---\n\n### 4. Template System (`/workspace/src/core/templates.ts`)\n\nTwo factory functions:\n\n**`createDefaultTemplate(): Template`** -- name: `'default'`\nRenders an HTML document with:\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>{data.title} | {data.siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <article>\n    <h1>{data.title}</h1>\n    {if data.date: <time>{data.date}</time>}\n    <div class=\"content\">{content}</div>\n  </article>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n**`createListTemplate(): Template`** -- name: `'list'`\nRenders an HTML document with:\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>{data.title} | {data.siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>{data.title}</h1>\n  <div class=\"list\">{content}</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\nThe barrel export at `/workspace/src/core/index.ts` re-exports: `BuildEngine`, `createDefaultTemplate`, `createListTemplate`, and all types (`BuildContext`, `ContentFile`, `Plugin`, `PluginHooks`, `SiteConfig`, `Template`).\n\n---\n\n### 5. Core Tests (`/workspace/tests/core.test.ts`) -- All 15 Tests\n\nUses helpers: `makeFile(overrides)` (defaults: slug `'test-post'`, title `'Test Post'`, content `'<p>Hello world</p>'`, metadata `{}`) and `makePlugin(overrides)` (defaults: name `'test-plugin'`, version `'1.0.0'`, dependencies `[]`, hooks `{}`).\n\n| # | Test Name | What It Verifies |\n|---|-----------|-----------------|\n| 1 | `registers plugins` | After `registerPlugin`, `getPlugins()` has length 1 and correct name |\n| 2 | `registers templates` | After `registerTemplate(createDefaultTemplate())`, templates map has `'default'` |\n| 3 | `builds with default template and renders HTML` | Output contains `<!DOCTYPE html>`, title `'My Post'`, content `<p>Content here</p>`, site title `'Test Site'` |\n| 4 | `builds with list template and renders list HTML` | Output contains `<!DOCTYPE html>`, title `'My List'`, `<div class=\"list\">`, and list content |\n| 5 | `outputs raw content when no matching template` | With no template registered, output is raw `<p>Raw content</p>` |\n| 6 | `calls plugin beforeBuild hook` | A `beforeBuild` hook setting `called = true` is invoked |\n| 7 | `calls plugin transformContent hook to transform files` | Hook uppercases content; result is `'HELLO'` |\n| 8 | `calls plugin afterBuild hook` | An `afterBuild` hook setting `called = true` is invoked |\n| 9 | `executes plugins in dependency order` | Plugin `b` depends on `a`; resolved order is `['a', 'b']` |\n| 10 | `throws on circular dependency` | `a -> b -> a` throws `'Circular dependency'` |\n| 11 | `throws on missing dependency` | `a -> missing` throws `'Missing dependency'` |\n| 12 | `applies multiple plugins transformContent in order` | Two plugins append `[first]` and `[second]`; result is `'start [first] [second]'` |\n| 13 | `provides shared data store in build context` | `beforeBuild` sets `ctx.data.set('key', 'value')`; verified after build |\n| 14 | `retains file metadata through build` | File with `metadata: {author:'Alice', category:'tech'}`, `date: '2024-01-01'`, `tags: ['js','node']` is preserved |\n| 15 | `produces empty output for empty file list` | Build with `[]` files yields `output.size === 0` and `files.length === 0` |\n\n---\n\n### 6. All Plugin Test Files -- Complete Details\n\n#### 6A. `markdown-ext.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImport: `createMarkdownExtPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/markdown-ext.js`\n\n| # | Test | Input Content | Expectations |\n|---|------|--------------|-------------|\n| 1 | `converts basic markdown to HTML` | `'# Hello\\n\\nThis is a **bold** paragraph.'` | Contains `<h1>`, contains `'Hello'`, contains `<strong>bold</strong>` |\n| 2 | `handles footnotes with [^1] syntax` | `'Some text[^1] here.\\n\\n[^1]: This is the footnote.'` | Contains `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>` |\n| 3 | `renders footnote section at bottom of content` | `'Text[^1] and more[^2].\\n\\n[^1]: First note.\\n[^2]: Second note.'` | Contains `<section class=\"footnotes\">`, `<li id=\"fn-1\">First note.</li>`, `<li id=\"fn-2\">Second note.</li>` |\n| 4 | `converts :::note container to admonition div` | `':::note\\nThis is a note.\\n:::'` | Contains `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">`, contains `'This is a note.'` |\n| 5 | `converts :::warning container to admonition div` | `':::warning\\nBe careful!\\n:::'` | Contains `<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\">`, contains `'Be careful!'` |\n| 6 | `converts :::tip container to admonition div` | `':::tip\\nHelpful hint.\\n:::'` | Contains `<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">`, contains `'Helpful hint.'` |\n| 7 | `preserves existing HTML in content` | `'<div class=\"custom\">Already HTML</div>'` | Contains `'Already HTML'` |\n| 8 | `handles empty content` | `''` | `result.content` is defined |\n\nKey implementation details: Must use the `marked` library for Markdown-to-HTML. Must pre-process footnotes (`[^N]` -> `<sup><a href=\"#fn-N\">N</a></sup>`, collect definitions, render a `<section class=\"footnotes\"><ol>...</ol></section>` at the end). Must pre-process `:::type ... :::` blocks into `<div class=\"admonition admonition-{type}\">...content...</div>`.\n\n---\n\n#### 6B. `asset-pipeline.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImport: `createAssetPipelinePlugin` from `../../src/plugins/asset-pipeline.js`\n\n| # | Test | Input | Expectations |\n|---|------|-------|-------------|\n| 1 | `rewrites relative image URLs to /assets/ path` | `<img src=\"./image.png\" alt=\"test\">` | Contains `src=\"/assets/image.png\"`, does NOT contain `src=\"./image.png\"` |\n| 2 | `rewrites relative link URLs to /assets/ path` | `<a href=\"./doc.pdf\">Download</a>` | Contains `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`, does NOT contain `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` |\n| 3 | `leaves absolute URLs unchanged` | `<img src=\"https://cdn.example.com/image.png\">` | Contains original absolute URL |\n| 4 | `generates asset manifest in ctx.data` | `<img src=\"./photo.jpg\">` | `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` has `assets` containing `'photo.jpg'` |\n| 5 | `handles files with no asset references` | `<p>No assets here</p>` | Content unchanged: `'<p>No assets here</p>'` |\n| 6 | `handles multiple assets in one file` | `<img src=\"./a.png\"><img src=\"./b.jpg\"><a href=\"./c.pdf\">link</a>` | Manifest assets contains `'a.png'`, `'b.jpg'`, `'c.pdf'` |\n| 7 | `asset manifest includes all discovered assets` | Two files: `<img src=\"./one.png\">`, `<img src=\"./two.png\">` (called sequentially on same ctx) | Manifest has length 2, contains both |\n| 8 | `does not double-process already-rewritten URLs` | `<img src=\"/assets/image.png\">` | Content unchanged `'<img src=\"/assets/image.png\">'`; manifest is undefined or has 0 assets |\n\nKey details: Rewrites `./filename` to `/assets/filename` in both `src` and `href` attributes. Stores `{ assets: string[] }` at key `'asset-manifest'` in `ctx.data`. Must accumulate assets across multiple calls on the same context.\n\n---\n\n#### 6C. `syntax-highlight.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImport: `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/syntax-highlight.js`\n\n| # | Test | Input | Expectations |\n|---|------|-------|-------------|\n| 1 | `adds language class to code blocks` | `<pre><code class=\"language-javascript\">const x = 1;</code></pre>` | Contains `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"` |\n| 2 | `adds data-language attribute to pre tags` | `<pre><code class=\"language-python\">print(\"hi\")</code></pre>` | Contains `data-language=\"python\"` |\n| 3 | `handles multiple code blocks in one file` | Two blocks: `language-js` and `language-py` | Contains `data-language=\"js\"` and `data-language=\"py\"` |\n| 4 | `handles code block with no language specified` | `<pre><code>plain code</code></pre>` | Content unchanged exactly; no `highlighted` class added |\n| 5 | `adds highlighted class to processed blocks` | `<pre><code class=\"language-rust\">fn main() {}</code></pre>` | Contains `'highlighted'` |\n| 6 | `preserves code block content` | `<pre><code class=\"language-ts\">const x: number = 42;</code></pre>` | Contains `'const x: number = 42;'` |\n| 7 | `handles empty code blocks` | `<pre><code class=\"language-js\"></code></pre>` | Contains `data-language=\"js\"` and `'highlighted'` |\n| 8 | `does not modify inline code` | `<p>Use <code>console.log()</code> for debugging.</p>` | Content unchanged exactly; no `highlighted` class |\n\nKey details: Only processes `<pre><code class=\"language-XXX\">` patterns. Adds `highlighted` to the class list and adds `data-language=\"XXX\"` to the `<pre>` tag. Leaves `<code>` without `<pre>` wrapper and `<code>` without `language-` class untouched.\n\n---\n\n#### 6D. `taxonomy.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImport: `createTaxonomyPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/taxonomy.js`\n\n| # | Test | Input | Expectations |\n|---|------|-------|-------------|\n| 1 | `builds tag index from file tags` | 2 files: one with `['javascript','node']`, one with `['javascript']` | `taxonomy-tags` map: `javascript` has 2, `node` has 1 |\n| 2 | `generates tag listing pages in ctx.output` | 1 file tagged `['javascript']` | After `beforeBuild` + `afterBuild`: `output.has('tags/javascript.html')` is true, content contains `'Post 1'` |\n| 3 | `handles files with no tags` | 1 file with no tags | Tag map size is 0 |\n| 4 | `handles files with multiple tags` | 1 file tagged `['js','node','web']` | Tag map size is 3, has all three keys |\n| 5 | `tag pages list all files with that tag` | 2 files both tagged `['tech']` | Tag page `'tags/tech.html'` contains both `'First Post'` and `'Second Post'` |\n| 6 | `stores tag map in ctx.data` | 1 file tagged `['alpha']` | `ctx.data.has('taxonomy-tags')` is true |\n| 7 | `handles empty file list` | Empty array | After both hooks: tag map size is 0 |\n| 8 | `tags are case-normalized to lowercase` | Two files: one tagged `['JavaScript']`, other `['JAVASCRIPT']` | Map has `'javascript'` with length 2; does NOT have `'JavaScript'` or `'JAVASCRIPT'` |\n\nKey details: Uses `beforeBuild` to scan `ctx.files` and build a `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` stored at key `'taxonomy-tags'` in `ctx.data`. Tags are lowercased. Uses `afterBuild` to generate HTML tag pages at `tags/{tag}.html` in `ctx.output`, listing all post titles for that tag.\n\n---\n\n#### 6E. `rss-feed.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImport: `createRssFeedPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/rss-feed.js`\nDependencies: `['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy']`\n\n| # | Test | Input | Expectations |\n|---|------|-------|-------------|\n| 1 | `generates valid RSS 2.0 XML` | 1 file with date | Output `'feed.xml'` contains `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>`, `</rss>` |\n| 2 | `feed items contain HTML content not raw markdown` | File with HTML content `<p>This is <strong>HTML</strong> content</p>` | Feed contains `<![CDATA[<p>This is <strong>HTML</strong> content</p>]]>` |\n| 3 | `feed items include category tags from taxonomy` | File tagged `['javascript']`; `ctx.data` has `'taxonomy-tags'` map | Feed contains `<category>javascript</category>` |\n| 4 | `feed includes channel title from config` | Any file | Feed contains `<title>Test Site</title>` |\n| 5 | `feed items sorted by date newest first` | 3 files: dates `2023-01-01`, `2024-06-15`, `2024-01-01` | In feed XML, `'New Post'` index < `'Mid Post'` index < `'Old Post'` index |\n| 6 | `handles files without dates` | File with no date | Feed contains `'No Date Post'`; does NOT contain `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>` |\n| 7 | `feed link uses baseUrl from config` | 1 file slug `'post-1'` | Feed contains `<link>https://example.com</link>` (channel) and `<link>https://example.com/post-1.html</link>` (item) |\n\n---\n\n#### 6F. `search-index.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImport: `createSearchIndexPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/search-index.js`\nDependencies: `['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight']`\n\n| # | Test | Input | Expectations |\n|---|------|-------|-------------|\n| 1 | `generates search-index.json in ctx.output` | 1 file | `output.has('search-index.json')` is true |\n| 2 | `index entries have title, slug, and plain text content` | File with `<p>Some text here</p>` | Parsed JSON entry: `slug === 'my-post'`, `title === 'My Post'`, `content === 'Some text here'` |\n| 3 | `HTML tags stripped from indexed content` | `<h1>Title</h1><p>This is <strong>bold</strong> text.</p>` | Content has no `<` or `>` chars; contains `'bold'` and `'text'` |\n| 4 | `code blocks included in searchable text` | `<pre><code class=\"language-js\">const x = 1;</code></pre>` | Content contains `'const x = 1;'` |\n| 5 | `handles empty file list` | Empty array | Parsed JSON equals `[]` |\n| 6 | `search index is valid JSON` | 2 files | Parsing does not throw; result is array of length 2 |\n| 7 | `index entries include tags if present` | File with `tags: ['js', 'web']` | Parsed entry `tags` equals `['js', 'web']` |\n\n---\n\n#### 6G. `sitemap.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImport: `createSitemapPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/sitemap.js`\nDependencies: `['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']`\n\n| # | Test | Input | Expectations |\n|---|------|-------|-------------|\n| 1 | `generates sitemap.xml in ctx.output` | Output map with `'post-1.html'` | `output.has('sitemap.xml')` is true |\n| 2 | `includes all content page URLs` | Output map with `'post-1.html'` and `'post-2.html'` | Sitemap contains both full URLs with baseUrl prefix |\n| 3 | `includes taxonomy tag page URLs` | Output has `'tags/javascript.html'`; data has taxonomy-tags map | Sitemap contains `'https://example.com/tags/javascript.html'` |\n| 4 | `includes feed.xml URL` | Output has `'feed.xml'` | Sitemap contains `'https://example.com/feed.xml'` |\n| 5 | `URLs use baseUrl from config` | Output has `'about.html'` | Sitemap contains `'https://example.com/about.html'` |\n| 6 | `sitemap is valid XML structure` | Output has `'post.html'` | Contains `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<urlset`, `</urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>` |\n| 7 | `handles site with no tag pages` | Output has `'post.html'`; no taxonomy data | Contains post URL; does NOT contain `'/tags/'` |\n\n---\n\n#### 6H. `dev-server.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImport: `createDevServerPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/dev-server.js`\nDependencies: `['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']`\n\nLocal interface defined in test:\n```typescript\ninterface DevServerConfig {\n  port: number;\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n  assetPaths: string[];\n  searchIndexPath: string;\n}\n```\n\n| # | Test | Input | Expectations |\n|---|------|-------|-------------|\n| 1 | `stores dev-server-config in ctx.data` | Empty ctx | `ctx.data.has('dev-server-config')` is true |\n| 2 | `config includes port setting` | Empty ctx | `config.port` is defined and `typeof` is `'number'` |\n| 3 | `config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline` | Data has `'asset-manifest': { assets: ['image.png', 'style.css'] }` | `config.assetPaths` contains both; routes filtered by `handler === 'asset'` has length >= 2 |\n| 4 | `config includes search index path` | Output has `'search-index.json'` | `config.searchIndexPath === '/search-index.json'` |\n| 5 | `config includes content routes` | Output has `'post-1.html'` and `'post-2.html'` | Routes filtered by `handler === 'static'` has length 2 |\n| 6 | `default port is 3000` | Empty ctx | `config.port === 3000` |\n| 7 | `handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully` | Empty ctx (no asset-manifest) | `config.assetPaths` equals `[]` |\n\n---\n\n### 7. `package.json` Details\n\n- **Name:** `bench-ssg-toolkit`\n- **Type:** `\"module\"` (ESM)\n- **Main:** `dist/core/index.js`\n- **Scripts:**\n  - `build` -> `tsc`\n  - `lint` -> `eslint src/ tests/`\n  - `test` -> `vitest run`\n- **Dev Dependencies:** `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin ^7.18.0`, `@typescript-eslint/parser ^7.18.0`, `eslint ^8.57.1`, `typescript ^5.9.3`, `vitest ^2.1.9`\n- **Dependencies:** `@types/express ^5.0.6`, `@types/marked ^5.0.2`, `express ^5.2.1`, `marked ^17.0.2`\n\n---\n\n### 8. Configuration Files\n\n**`tsconfig.json`:**\n- `strict: true`\n- `target: \"ES2022\"`, `module: \"Node16\"`, `moduleResolution: \"Node16\"`\n- `outDir: \"./dist\"`, `rootDir: \"./src\"`\n- `declaration: true`, `esModuleInterop: true`, `skipLibCheck: true`\n- Includes `src/**/*`\n\n**`.eslintrc.cjs`:**\n- Parser: `@typescript-eslint/parser`\n- Plugins: `@typescript-eslint`\n- Extends: `eslint:recommended`, `plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended`\n- `ecmaVersion: 2022`, `sourceType: \"module\"`\n- Custom rule: `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars` set to `error` with `argsIgnorePattern: '^_'` and `varsIgnorePattern: '^_'`\n- Env: `node: true`, `es2022: true`\n\n**`vitest.config.ts`:**\n- `globals: true` (no need to import `describe`/`it`/`expect`, though the tests do import them)\n- `testTimeout: 10000` (10 seconds)\n\n---\n\n### Plugin Dependency Graph (from TASK.md)\n\n```\nWave 1 (no dependencies):\n  markdown-ext, asset-pipeline, syntax-highlight, taxonomy\n\nWave 2 (depend on Wave 1):\n  rss-feed       -> [markdown-ext, taxonomy]\n  s